, "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "lazy", "type": null, "default": "..."}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["Get nested index from collection\n\n# Examples\n\n```pycon\n>>> nested_get(1, 'abc')\n'b'\n>>> nested_get([1, 0], 'abc')\n['b', 'a']\n>>> nested_get([[1, 0], [0, 1]], 'abc')\n[['b', 'a'], ['a', 'b']]\n```\n"]}, {"name": "partd.utils.flatten", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "seq", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["```pycon\n>>> list(flatten([1]))\n[1]\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> list(flatten([[1, 2], [1, 2]]))\n[1, 2, 1, 2]\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> list(flatten([[[1], [2]], [[1], [2]]]))\n[1, 2, 1, 2]\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> list(flatten(((1, 2), (1, 2)))) # Don't flatten tuples\n[(1, 2), (1, 2)]\n```\n\n```pycon\n>>> list(flatten((1, 2, [3, 4]))) # support heterogeneous\n[1, 2, 3, 4]\n```\n"]}, {"name": "partd.utils.suffix", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "term", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["suffix a key with a suffix\n\nWorks if they key is a string or a tuple\n\n```pycon\n>>> suffix('x', '.dtype')\n'x.dtype'\n>>> suffix(('a', 'b', 'c'), '.dtype')\n('a', 'b', 'c.dtype')\n```\n"]}, {"name": "partd.utils.extend", "asynchronous": false, "params": [{"name": "key", "type": null, "default": null}, {"name": "term", "type": null, "default": null}], "returns": null, "documentation": ["extend a key with a another element in a tuple\n\nWorks if they key is a string or a tuple\n\n```pycon\n>>> extend('x', '.dtype')\n('x', '.dtype')\n>>> extend(('a', 'b', 'c'), '.dtype')\n('a', 'b', 'c', '.dtype')\n```\n"]}], "variables": [], "classes": [], "exports": []}, {"name": "partd._version", "documentation": ["This file was generated by 'versioneer.py' (0.29) from", "revision-control system data, or from the parent directory name of an", "unpacked source archive. Distribution tarballs contain a pre-generated copy", "of this file."], "